						<summary>

						<p>On a slab set up in front of the Siddhēśvara temple in the village.</p>						

						<p>Eastern Chāḷukya: Sarvalōkāśraya Vishṇuvardhana, 5th year.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Bahudhānya, Kārttīka śu. 5, Sunday.</p>						

						<p>Records the gift of 100 <hi rend="italic">gadyāṇas</hi> and 18 <hi rend="italic">puṭṭis</hi> of land to the temple of Siddhēśvara by Kṟomuala Lōkamayya and Jeṭṭimayya of Guṇḍabāḍu. In characters of the 7th century A.D. (Pub: <hi rend="italic">Corpus of Inscriptions in Telangana District,</hi> Part IV, No. 1.)</p>						

						</summary>
